title: Zacks: Analysts Anticipate Tableau Software Inc Class A (DATA) Will Post Earnings of -$0.09 Per Share
content: Wall Street analysts predict that Tableau Software Inc Class A (NYSE:DATA) will announce earnings per share of ($0.09) for the current quarter, Zacks reports. Ten analysts have provided estimates for Tableau Software Inc Class A’s earnings, with the highest EPS estimate coming in at $0.02 and the lowest estimate coming in at ($0.13). Tableau Software Inc Class A posted earnings of $0.10 per share during the same quarter last year, which would indicate a negative year over year growth rate of 190%. The company is expected to announce its next earnings results  on Wednesday, August 1st.    On average, analysts expect that Tableau Software Inc Class A will report full year earnings of ($0.15) per share for the current fiscal year, with EPS estimates ranging from ($0.23) to $0.10. For the next financial year, analysts forecast that the firm will report earnings of $0.35 per share, with EPS estimates ranging from $0.18 to $0.59. Zacks’ earnings per share calculations are a mean average based on a survey of sell-side research analysts that cover Tableau Software Inc Class A.         Tableau Software Inc Class A (NYSE:DATA) last issued its quarterly earnings results on Wednesday, May 2nd. The software company reported ($0.19) earnings per share for the quarter, missing the Zacks’ consensus estimate of ($0.18) by ($0.01). The business had revenue of $224.00 million for the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $217.92 million. Tableau Software Inc Class A had a negative return on equity of 23.86% and a negative net margin of 19.21%. The firm’s revenue for the quarter was up 12.0% on a year-over-year basis. During the same quarter in the prior year, the company earned $0.03 EPS.    A number of analysts recently weighed in on DATA shares. Zacks Investment Research cut shares of Tableau Software Inc Class A from a “hold” rating to a “sell” rating in a research note on Friday, February 2nd. Barclays  reiterated a “buy” rating and set a $102.00 price target on shares of Tableau Software Inc Class A in a research note on Sunday, April 22nd. UBS Group  set a $108.00 price target on shares of Tableau Software Inc Class A and gave the stock a “buy” rating in a research note on Wednesday, February 14th. Maxim Group upgraded shares of Tableau Software Inc Class A from a “sell” rating to a “hold” rating and increased their price target for the stock from $40.00 to $88.00 in a research note on Friday, February 2nd. Finally, Bank of America raised their target price on shares of Tableau Software Inc Class A from $90.00 to $108.00 and gave the stock a “buy” rating in a research note on Friday, February 2nd. Two investment analysts have rated the stock with a sell rating, thirteen have issued  a hold rating, thirteen have assigned  a buy rating and one  has assigned  a strong buy rating to the company. Tableau Software Inc Class A presently has a consensus rating of “Hold” and an average target price of $94.48.  In other Tableau Software Inc Class A news, EVP Keenan Michael Conder sold 2,500 shares of the firm’s stock in a transaction dated Monday, March 5th. The shares were sold at an average price of $84.39, for a total transaction of $210,975.00. Following the completion of the transaction, the executive vice president now directly owns 119,842 shares in the company, valued at approximately $10,113,466.38. The transaction was disclosed in a legal filing with the Securities & Exchange Commission, which is accessible through this hyperlink . Also, CEO Adam Selipsky sold 1,600 shares of the firm’s stock in a transaction dated Monday, March 5th. The shares were sold at an average price of $82.54, for a total transaction of $132,064.00. Following the transaction, the chief executive officer now owns 294,949 shares of the company’s stock, valued at $24,345,090.46. The disclosure for this sale can be found here . Insiders sold a total of 933,961 shares of company stock valued at $86,051,790 in the last quarter. Insiders own  28.98% of the company’s stock.    Large investors have recently bought and sold shares of the business. American International Group Inc. purchased a new position in  Tableau Software Inc Class A during the 4th quarter valued at about $105,000.  Diversified Trust Co purchased a new position in  Tableau Software Inc Class A during the 1st quarter valued at about $204,000.  LPL Financial LLC purchased a new position in  Tableau Software Inc Class A during the 1st quarter valued at about $206,000.  Mitsubishi UFJ Securities Holdings Co. Ltd. purchased a new position in  Tableau Software Inc Class A during the 1st quarter valued at about $209,000.  Finally, CIBC Asset Management Inc purchased a new position in  Tableau Software Inc Class A during the 1st quarter valued at about $210,000. Hedge funds and other institutional investors own  80.47% of the company’s stock.    NYSE:DATA traded down $0.34 during trading hours on Friday, reaching $98.53. 1,023,162 shares of the company’s stock were exchanged, compared to its average volume of 908,855. The stock has a market cap of $8.10 billion, a P/E ratio of -42.11 and a beta of 0.78. Tableau Software Inc Class A has a 1-year low of $57.25 and a 1-year high of $99.79.    Tableau Software Inc Class A Company Profile    Tableau Software, Inc provides business analytics software products. It offers Tableau Desktop, an analytics product that empowers people to access and analyze data; and Tableau Server, a business intelligence platform with data management and scalability to foster sharing of analytics, as well as to enhance the dissemination of information in an organization and promote decision-making.
